	\end{subfigure}
	\begin{subfigure}[b]{\linewidth}
		\centering
		\includegraphics[width=0.8\linewidth]{../Meridional/heatmap/Standard/250.png}
		\caption{Equirectangular Projection,  250 Millibars}
	\end{subfigure}
	\caption{Equirectangular Projection}
\end{figure}
\noindent Across both of the levels, we see northward and southward wind in a checked pattern. For the most part, the longitudinal differences in meridional wind are consequences of the circulations associated with cyclones and anticyclones. The angle of this propagation is due to the influence of the Coriolis force. 
